    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2009-01-28</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2009-02-25T22:27:12Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>State Temporary Economic Priority (STEP) Act - Authorizes states to transfer or consolidate funds made available to them under certain federal transportation, education, and job training programs: (1) beginning with the calendar quarter after the United States experiences economic growth at an annual rate of less than 1% for two consecutive calendar quarters; and (2) continuing until 18 months after it experiences economic growth at an annual rate of 1% or more for two consecutive calendar quarters.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>State Temporary Economic Priority (STEP) Act</title>
